The paper proposes a novel approach to multi-label learning that involves collaboration between labels, which is a common problem in machine learning. The method involves learning label correlations via sparse reconstruction in the label space and integrating them into model training. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). However, given the focus on machine learning and the use of sparse reconstruction, cs.LG is the most likely category, followed by cs.CV and cs.AI.
